                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/42.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My November 17. Chinese merchants under order of arrest have taken out writs of
                    habeas corpus against the Government of Panama which have been referred to the
                    Supreme Court, thus directly testing constitutionality of Law 50. Inventories
                    completed. Chinese have opened shops. Situation greatly relieved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
